  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BAR AMA BARO (New Somalia Education Activity)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(Somalia):  Bar Ama Baro (BaB, &quot;Teach or Learn&quot; in Somali), will increase.access to quality education for out-of-school children and youth aged 8-15 in.targeted regions via increased student enrollment; school safety; literacy,.numeracy, and socio-emotional skills acquisition; greater government capacity.to regulate these schools; and youth involvement in BaB&apos;s education efforts..Community teachers, especially female teachers, will be recruited and.trained. Teaching materials will be developed and disseminated, complementing.the government&apos;s new formal curriculum. Innovative technology, critical because.of COVID-19&apos;s disruption to Somalia&apos;s education efforts, will ensure access to.education.  BaB will foster positive gender norms and reduce educational.barriers for girls and boys. Community efforts to support education - from.advocacy, mobilization and protection of vulnerable students - will build.resilience to withstand al-Shabaab&apos;s ideological attacks and coercive recruitment.techniques.  USAID will assist the government and the private sector to.develop accelerated education programming, policies on teacher qualifications.and instructional time, and academic standards. This latter effort will lead to.accreditation of BaB schools, and certification of students so that they may transition.into formal schools at the right level. As a result of the COVID-19 pandemic,.BaB put out risk and community messaging, including simple education messages,.to ensure students remain connected to learning while schools are closed. While.the Ministry of Education intends to open schools in the 2020-2021 school year,.should schools remain closed or be forced to re-close, BaB is planning for a.number of different scenarios to keep students learning during the crisis.  .. ... ........ ..</narrative>
  </description>
